TY  - JOUR
T1  - U.S.-Japanese Manufacturing Equity Relationships
AU  - Swan, Peter F.
AU  - Ettlie, John E.
Y1  - 1997/04/01
PY  - 1997
DA  - 1997/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256891
DO  - 10.5465/256891
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 462
EP  - 479
VL  - 40
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We explored the differences between the joint venture, total ownership, and partial equity positions used by Japanese companies investing in U.S. manufacturing via a secondary data analysis. Partial ownership was used significantly more often in high-technology industries. Joint ventures were significantly more likely to be used in politically sensitive industries and in new entities, and when the Japanese partner had experience with the product.
AB  - We explored the differences between the joint venture, total ownership, and partial equity positions used by Japanese companies investing in U.S. manufacturing via a secondary data analysis. Partial ownership was used significantly more often in high-technology industries. Joint ventures were significantly more likely to be used in politically sensitive industries and in new entities, and when the Japanese partner had experience with the product.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256891
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256891
Y2  - 2026/04/24
